This paper deals with the analysis of geometric graphs, specifically theta graphs, which are commonly used in wireless networking, motion planning, and real-time animation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses the average degree of theta graphs, which is a metric commonly used in network analysis, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the concentration of edges in theta graphs, which is a topic related to probability and statistics, suggesting that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper's focus on geometric graphs and their applications suggests that it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
